main event: Civilians observed three satellite-like objects rapidly moving across the sky in West Milton, Kettering, and Fairborn, Ohio on March 28, 1966.
interesting points: The objects appeared similar to satellites and were reported to be moving at a rapid rate of speed,The sightings lasted for 5-10 minutes each,Over 30 satellites were confirmed to be orbiting Earth at that time,The observations were consistent with what one would expect from a satellite,Visual confirmation was made by civilians.
witness description: a civilian resident in West Milton, Ohio
